President Obama has announced his intention to appoint three individuals to key Administration posts. 

1. Dr. Manuel Gomez: He is a Professor of Physics at the University of Puerto Rico and the Director and Founder of the Universityâ€™s Resource Center for Science and Engineering. He has also served as a member of the National Science Foundation Directorate for Education and Human Resources Advisory Committee. Dr. Gomez holds a B.S. in Physics from the University of Puerto Rico and a Ph.D. in Theoretical Physics from Cornell University.

2. Dr. Sara Lundquist: She is the Vice President of Student Services at Santa Ana College and has been employed there for over 33 years. Dr. Lundquist has served as the Principal Investigator for numerous grant and research projects and has received her Ph.D. in Higher Education from Claremont Graduate University.

3. Katrina L. Peebles: She serves on the board of directors of The Peebles Corporation, a real estate company. She has also been involved in organizations such as The Vizcayans, where she is currently a board member. Ms. Peebles received a B.S. in Journalism from the University of Colorado at Boulder.

These individuals will be appointed to the President's Advisory Commission on Educational Excellence for Hispanics and the President's Advisory Committee on Arts for the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts. President Obama expressed his gratitude to these appointees and looks forward to working with them in the future.